00:07:45.249 --> 00:07:49.879
So, by the end of 1944, the Allies were advancing
from the West and the Russian Red Army was

00:07:49.879 --> 00:07:54.439
advancing from the East and then, the last-ditch
German offensive at the battle of the Bulge

00:07:54.439 --> 00:08:00.979
in the winter of 1944-1945 failed. Mussolini
was executed in April of 1945. Hitler committed

00:08:00.979 --> 00:08:06.430
suicide at the end of that month. And, on
May 8, 1945 the Allies declared victory in

00:08:06.430 --> 00:08:09.370
Europe after Germany surrendered unconditionally.

00:08:09.370 --> 00:08:13.129
Three months later, the United States dropped
the only two nuclear weapons ever deployed

00:08:13.129 --> 00:08:16.539
in war, Japan surrendered, and World War II
was over.

00:08:16.539 --> 00:08:22.379
The war had a definite cause: unbridled military
expansion by Germany, Japan, and, to a small

00:08:22.379 --> 00:08:26.180
extent, Italy. Now, it’s easy to claim that
Hitler was crazy or evil, and, in fact, he

00:08:26.180 --> 00:08:30.490
was certainly both, but that doesn’t explain
the Nazis decision to invade Russia, and it

00:08:30.490 --> 00:08:33.990
sure doesn’t explain Japan’s decision
to bomb Pearl Harbor.

00:08:33.990 --> 00:08:37.620
And there are many possible explanations beyond
mere evil; but the most interesting one, to

00:08:37.620 --> 00:08:41.419
me, involves food. Hitler had a number of
reasons for wanting to expand Germany’s

00:08:41.419 --> 00:08:46.000
territory, but he often talked about Lebensraum
or living space for the German people. German

00:08:46.000 --> 00:08:50.060
agriculture was really inefficiently organized
into lots of small farms, and that meant that

00:08:50.060 --> 00:08:54.430
Germany needed a lot of land in order to be
self-sufficient in food production.

00:08:54.430 --> 00:08:58.430
The plan was to take Poland, the Ukraine,
and Eastern Russia, and then resettle that

00:08:58.430 --> 00:09:02.850
land with lots of Germans, so that it could
feed German people. This was called the Hunger

00:09:02.850 --> 00:09:07.380
Plan because the plan called for 20 million
people to starve to death. Many would be the

00:09:07.380 --> 00:09:12.220
Poles, Ukrainians, and Russians who’d previously
lived on the land. The rest would be Europe’s

00:09:12.220 --> 00:09:14.269
Jews, who would be worked to death.

00:09:14.269 --> 00:09:18.880
Six million Jews were killed by the Nazis,
many by starvation, but many through a chillingly

00:09:18.880 --> 00:09:23.320
planned effort of extermination in death camps.
These death camps can be distinguished from

00:09:23.320 --> 00:09:28.279
concentration camps or labor camps in that
their primary purpose was extermination of

00:09:28.279 --> 00:09:33.440
Jews, Roma people, communists, homosexuals,
disabled people, and others that the Nazis

00:09:33.440 --> 00:09:37.660
deemed unfit. Some historians believe that
the Nazis opened the death camps because the

00:09:37.660 --> 00:09:41.070
Jews weren’t dying as fast as The Hunger
Plan had intended.

00:09:41.070 --> 00:09:45.760
This was a sickening plan, but it made a kind
of demented sense. Rather than becoming more

00:09:45.760 --> 00:09:50.910
involved in global trade, as the British had,
the Germans would feed themselves by taking

00:09:50.910 --> 00:09:54.089
land and killing the people who’d previously
lived there.

00:09:54.089 --> 00:09:57.990
Similarly, Japan, at the beginning of the
war, was suffering from an acute fear of food

00:09:57.990 --> 00:10:02.130
shortage because its agricultural sector was
having trouble keeping up with population

00:10:02.130 --> 00:10:06.050
growth. And the Japanese too, sought to expand
their agricultural holdings by, for instance,

00:10:06.050 --> 00:10:07.500
resettling farmers in Korea.

00:10:07.509 --> 00:10:11.690
So while it’s tempting to say that World
War II was about the Allies fighting for democratic

00:10:11.690 --> 00:10:17.509
ideals against the totalitarian militaristic
imperialism of the fascist Axis powers, it

00:10:17.509 --> 00:10:22.509
just doesn’t hold up to scrutiny. For instance,
a hugely important Allied power, Stalin’s

00:10:22.509 --> 00:10:27.339
Soviet Union, was, like, the least democratic
place, ever. Stan just said that was hyperbole,

00:10:27.339 --> 00:10:32.209
but it’s not. Stalin’s Soviet Union is
tied with all of the other completely undemocratic

00:10:32.209 --> 00:10:37.290
countries for last place on the democracy
scale. It’s a big community there, at last

00:10:37.290 --> 00:10:39.070
place, but they’re definitely in there somewhere.

00:10:39.070 --> 00:10:43.399
And, by far, the biggest imperialists of the
war were the British. They couldn’t have

00:10:43.399 --> 00:10:48.470
fed or clothed themselves - or resisted the
Nazis - without their colonies and commonwealth.

00:10:48.470 --> 00:10:53.980
So, why is World War II so important? Well
first, it proved the old Roman adage homo homini

00:10:53.980 --> 00:11:00.920
lupus: Man is a wolf to man. This is seen most clearly
in the Holocaust, but all the statistics are staggering.

00:11:00.920 --> 00:11:04.440
More than a million Indian British subjects
died, mainly due to famine that could have

00:11:04.449 --> 00:11:08.820
been avoided if the British had redistributed
food. And their failure to do so helped convince

00:11:08.820 --> 00:11:13.589
Indians that the so-called superior civilization
of the British was a sham. More than a million

00:11:13.589 --> 00:11:19.870
Vietnamese died, mainly due to famine. 418,000
Americans. More than a million noncombatants

00:11:19.870 --> 00:11:26.250
in both Germany and Japan. And 20 million
people in the Soviet Union, most of them civilians.

00:11:26.250 --> 00:11:30.519
These civilians were targeted because they
helped sustain the war, mostly through industrial

00:11:30.519 --> 00:11:35.500
and agricultural production. In a total war,
when a nation is at war, not just its army,

00:11:35.500 --> 00:11:40.470
there is no such thing as a non-military target.
From the firebombing of Dresden to Tokyo to

00:11:40.470 --> 00:11:44.430
Hiroshima, the line between soldier and civilian
blurred.

00:11:44.430 --> 00:11:48.170
And then, of course, there is the Holocaust,
which horrifies us because the elements of

00:11:48.170 --> 00:11:55.029
Western progress - record-keeping, industrial
production, technology - were used to slaughter

00:11:55.029 --> 00:12:00.199
millions. World War II saw modern industrial
nations, which represented the best of the

00:12:00.199 --> 00:12:05.889
Enlightenment and the Scientific Revolution,
descend into once unimaginable cruelty.

00:12:05.889 --> 00:12:10.759
And what makes World War II such a historical
watershed is that in its wake, all of us - in

00:12:10.759 --> 00:12:16.399
the West or otherwise - were forced to question
whether Western dominance of this planet could,

00:12:16.399 --> 00:12:18.939
or should, be considered progress.

